title: Fanum on Growing Up in The Bronx, Joining AMP, YouTube Hustle & More
description:
JustFanum speaks on his rise to content success, being from the Bronx, finding different ways to be successful, AMP, Youtube, Twitch police, and more!

-----
00:00 Intro
0:50 - Creating 2 different channels, toxic 2k community, people playing for 18hrs a day
2:57 - Started off trying to talk like the YouTubers he was watching, getting on his Bronx sh*t and things took off
5:45 - Starting to go hard on YouTube, starting his IRL streams, getting demonetized all the time at first
7:28 - Getting 800k views on videos, getting a strike for showing kids fighting
10:47 - Says black creators are watched by YouTube and Twitch police
12:42 - Flakko wants to know his biggest check, making 6 figures a month
18:24 - Not crossing lines with his pranks
19:22 - Says cancel culture isn’t real
21:31 - Always holding on to his roots, keeping his Honda Accord
22:02 - His Mom doesn't understand Youtube, his parents have PhDs
22:40 - Uses to take pictures of school books coz he couldn’t afford them, dropping out to do YouTube
26:02 - Being obsessed with what he does, being consistent
35:10 - Not letting negative comments get to you, more love than trolls
38:35 - Team10 vs Cloutgang beef, love Jake and Logan Paul new career trajectories
40:05 - AMP Rico is now living in Atlanta, difference between there and LA and New York
42:22 - When Teanna Trump came to the crib, pulling up in the Porsche, being proud of Kai Cenat
47:42 - Feeling like a lot of rappers are just custies, popping pills and doing dr*gs
49:36 - NYC mayor Eric Adams trying to stop Drill music from being played on radio
50:47 - Feeling safe when he’s in the hood, seeing guy get s___ on the corner, not being phased by it
53:36 - YouTubers vs Rappers
54:30 - YouTube groupies, not talking about famous chicks he’s smashed
55:39 - Asian Doll can do whatever she wants but she’s not the queen of the Bronx
57:19 - Bronx dudes get money and could afford to pay Asian Doll $10k
-----
